### **Power Stack & Gear System (Detailed)**

**To Upgrade a Coin:**
- **Level 1 → Level 2:** `Cap/Pop` action. Place one of your coins from your supply onto the target. **End your turn.**
- **Level 1 → Level 3:** `Cap/Pop` action. Place two coins from your supply onto the target. **Skip your next turn.**

**Maintenance Cost:**
- After moving a **Level 3+** coin, you must use a future `Bet/Place` action to put a coin in the position it vacated.

**Unlocked Abilities by Gear Level:**
- **GEAR 1:** `Bet/Place`, `Cap/Pop`
- **GEAR 2:** `Move/Rotate`, `Push/Pull`
- **GEAR 3:** `Swap/Jump`, `Mirror/Match`
- **GEAR 4:** `Reset/Clone`, `Ultim/Convert` (Gains Ultim Moves)


After upgrading or degrading, you cannot use the old gear's ability, so choose wisely. Also you can only use the first two instant ability, and on next turn you can chose one among the four abilities of the gear to play. Only Gear 1 is available for any Coin of any Gear Level.  


When on Gear 4, opponent can play twice per turn, not stackable. If both player are on Gear 4, opponent and player can only play once per turn, for fairplay.
